Oh yes, and weekends, I came home every weekend. My father used to pick me up on the train at Hackney station. On the Friday, and then - then he used to bring me on the Monday and let me out there. And - he went on t
o Liverpool Street to go to Shoreditch you see. And I only had to walk to my grandfather's and - it was only just round the corner from the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 What was it like staying with your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Oh, quite interesting, I used to be quite happy 
there and I used to play with my - grandpa used to - teach me games and - and - dominoes and all that sort of thing you know, I used to play with him, he was a dear old boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did he like children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Oh yes, he was very fond of children. He'd been m
arried three times. The first - his first wife had a boy and a girl - and that was before my father's time, and - when she - when they - I think they - that grandmother died - well she wasn't my grandmother, she died and then he married another one who wa
s
 well off, which was my mother - mother - my father's mother, and had a - two girls and my father, and then - she died, and then he married the governess that looked after the children. And that was what - what I call my grandmother although she really wa
sn't, I never met my real grandmother because she'd - died before we - were thought of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 So the one who had been the governess treated you as a grandchild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 The one, yes. She was a very nice old - well I say old, I don't suppose she was so old but 
she seemed so to me. And then she had a - trouble and died and he was left again so he - lost all three and then her sister came to look after him, and lived with him for quite a while until she wouldn't do it, then she - he came to Roydon and lived in a 
l
ittle cottage near my mother and father. My father wanted him to live with us but my mother wouldn't have it. So she - they had a cot - he had a cottage just nearby and a woman used to go in and see to him and - my mother used to - go in - mind you she wa
s quite friendly with him but he was a Liberal, and my mother was a Conservative.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did they both have strong views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 And they used to have terrific - arguments about it you know, really put me off politics for the rest of my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did your father follow his father in his views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 He was until my - my mother converted him to a Con - Conservative. She was very strong willed my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Why do you think she was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Well I don't - just because her father was I suppose, an
d - they'd always been, these farmers you know, this - where they lived - was - they were sort of the farm belonged to a squire, you know, that owned all the property and my - grandfather appa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 ently rented the farm you see off him and - so you always had t
o today to the squire, and of course he was a Conservative and so I suppose that's why - the farmers were more or less. You'd got to keep in with the owners of your property.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Do you think at that time people sometimes felt they risked losing their jobs if they didn't vote the same way?
