I quite think so, yes, they used to rule them a lot in those days you know. These - big - big people that owned all the land and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did your mother tell you about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did you ever remember that around Roydon when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 
Oh no, it wasn't like that there. No. There was one family called the Christy's, and they - tried to be a bit on the bossy side but we'd got to that stage then that you know you didn't take - well of co
urse we owned our own house and we were independent, but - you didn't - sort of today to these people then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did some people today to them do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Oh yes, they did, a lot of the village people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Who were these people, what was their job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 
Well I wouldn't know what they did, they were - you know, quite well off and had a big house and grounds and - they used to sort of boss the church and - do all the bazaars and things for the church and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Were they sort of big landowners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 No, well they didn't own a great lot, I think they were in business actually, I think the - husband went up to town - quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 But they sort of fancied themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Oh yes, they - they thought they were it you know. My mo
ther used to say anyway she - she - they used to annoy her considerably, 'cos - she was rather like - she would rather have liked to have run the church a bit you know. And the vicar was a bachelor so of course he couldn't stand up for himself poor man. H
e must have had an awful time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did your mother do anything in the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 
Oh yes, she - we used to go regularly and - she used to make a lot of - she used to make a lovely lot of - with this companion person, they used to make little pin cus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 ions
, like ladies in crinoline skirts, you know, and a china head on the top, with a little - all the lace, she used to make them beautiful, you know, all pink satin and green. I can always remember her doing those and putting lace right round to make frills,
 
you know, all the way up for the frocks, and they did these and filled them with sawdust and then put the - china head on the top. And - she used to sell those and then - we knew a man who lived opposite us who had a big drapery - wholesale draper sort of
 thing and she used to get round him to - give her a lot of things for the bazaar. I remember he gave her a lot of men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 s braces and I had to go round in the bazaar - selling these braces, I think about three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 
pence a - a pair you know and that sort of thing.
 But what annoyed my mother was that they - put these pin cushions in and they sold them for a penny each you know, and she - well it always happens in bazaars doesn't it, and she was most indignant and annoyed about this - and - so she packed it all up, 
