\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Had your mother ever talked to you about sex?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 No. Never. You know, I was only saying to my sister a few days ago - we never - I don't think we ever discussed anything like that wi
th my mother. She thought it was all disgusting. And - we never saw my mother or my father without any clothes on or - even - half clothed or anything, we never did. And when our like periods came and that, she just said, oh it's something that happens to
 you, I'll tell you about it when you're older, but she never did, I don't know how old I got to be before I heard but - I didn't -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 She didn't explain anything to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 No. We just got it from school when were at grammar school we - you know, how
 the girls talk you know, I expect that's all we - found out. Even when my brother was born it didn't dawn on us you know, 'cos we were - we went down to the school - the village schoolmaster and his wife were friends of my - my parents and - we went and 
s
tayed with them when my brother was born. Until - for about two or three days until things were sorted out. And she had her monthly nurse, she always had a nurse for a month every time she had a baby and - she lived in sort of you know and looked after he
r and the baby. And so - when we came back he was born and we didn't know anything about anything. Never - no - honestly we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 You never knew why you'd been sent away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 No, we didn't even know we were going to have a brother until it arrived. And t
he time - I remember the headmistress or the - schoolmaster's wife telling us you know that we'd got a little brother. We said, ugh. We didn't want any interruptions in our lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Were you very upset by that incident?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Well it did affect my heart
 apparently, because afterwards - a little while after that my brother - and - well - my mother - I don't know where May could have been, I suppose she didn't - she was away or a holiday or something, but I was left alone with my brother in the house whil
e
 she - my mother took my father down to the - station you see to catch the train, and when I went up to my brother he was lying in his cot, he was - he must have been about two, I don't know, and he was blue in the face you see, he was having convulsions 
a
nd I didn't know, and oh I was so terrified and I didn't know what to do and I ran out to - I had to go across our orchard to the next lady in the house - little house - next door, we always had a - sort of gap to go in to her because she was our only nei
g
hbour more or less, and she was bathing her baby, and I said, oh Mrs Fuller - come quickly, come quick, I said, the - Billy's all - gone all funny, I said, he's chocking and he's blue. She said, oh I can't hurry I've just got my Lily in the bath and - she
 
couldn't come but she said, you put plenty of water on the stove, and get plenty of hot water and then your mother'll be back soon, and that's all she bothered, she didn't come and help me or anything. And then fortunately my - my mother did return fairly
 soon after that and so of course she - knew it was convulsions only he was teething or something I suppose. And she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 plumped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 
 in - a hot bath.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Was the neighbour usually more helpful than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Yes, she was usually quite a - but - I suppose, you k
now, she'd got her baby in the bath and she couldn't sort of leave it and run and she couldn't take it with her as it was just having it's bath and - and I suppose she didn't really - realize what - was going on in a way. But I - I - often think of that b
e
cause it always stay in my mind 'cos it frightens, but I had a - a bad heart after that and the doctor said it was caused through these two - shocks you see. But - and also - I was eating - you know, I was a very fat child, because the trouble was my sist
e
r was very nervy and very delicate and she wouldn't eat, and then if anything was left my mother'd say, oh well you finish it up Bay, you see that was me. And I had to finish it, and I think that was wrong you know to do that because I was eating much to 
much for a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 But they weren't so conscious of diet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Oh no, they thought if you were fat you were lovely you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Fat babies used to be the pride?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Yes, used to adore them. I remember I - oh it was an awful time 'cos they just fed 
