Oh yes, we all did it and - he used to grow Henry Eckford's sweet peas, and - he won no end of silver medals and things for those. And it was my job to cut all the dead ones off or all those that were - under - two blooms you see, or
 two blooms and under, you have to cut those away and let the threes and fours grow you see for - showing purposes, and all the colours were in separate round circles, he grew them in circles with - silks and - well sticks I suppose he put up, canes it wo
uld - he'd put about four canes and bring them to a point and all these would run up them you see, and each colour had its own special round. Oh I used to be fed up with cutting sweet peas. Put me right off sweet peas, I didn't like them afterwards.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did you have your own little garden?
