Yes, we'd got a big old dog in the yard and a - and I had a little wire haired terrier of my own, called Jo - Joffat, after the - one of the - French Generals you know, cos this was after the war I had that, had my dog. And - we had - cat
s, several cats because - keep the rats and things down in - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 So it was at Roydon you had cats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Yes. But when we went to Clacton we didn't take anything with us, not animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 You were saying about the companion help that she didn't go out late at night because it was so dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 Yes, it was all country l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 anes, you couldn't go anywhere you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Did she sometimes have an afternoon off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4158279 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Oh yes, she'd have afternoon - well afternoon and an evening. Well, every week I think 
she had an afternoon. But - I think she used to get home before dark always because it's always nasty in the country when you - we all used to be at home you know after dark more or less.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Except for your one neighbour you were about two miles -
