Yes. The weekends and early mornings. We had two huge asparagus beds, and - we had a big cage with all soft fruits. And strawberries. We had a marvel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 ous place there for food, I mean we just kept ourselves in vegetables and - and fruit and - and the - over the - the stable and coach house there was a big loft and half of it of course was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 loft with the - for the pony, but this other - the part th
at was over the coach house was all - made in shelves and we stored all these apples you see. And pears and things right through the winter. Covered in hay or straw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7566687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 Can you tell me about the housework, the maid that came in every day, did she do all of it?
