n
o airing cupboard. And we used to - all our bedding was put under our mat - we had a mattress and a feather bed in those days, each bed. And our underwear and - the sheets belonging to each respective bed were put under these between this mattress and the
 
feather bed to keep aired. We always did that, and when - so when the beds were changed, you just took these off and you just got them from underneath the feather bed and - and put them on fresh. And that kept them aired 'cos you see there were no airing 
cupboards or anything then. Got to be aired and - my - my mother was very particular about having everything aired. Yes. And we all had - we had all our com}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16646281\charrsid15876756 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13448389\charrsid15876756 s and our bests and things were put under the - feather bed, and kept for the next week.
\par 
