s right through to Roydon station and right through home at the middle of the night. And once when I went to sing at his Masonic do I had to come home with him like that and of course my mother coul
dn't come and meet us because she couldn't leave the family at that time of night, and so we had to walk all the way there. But when we got older my sister used to drive the trap and - and meet us. Or meet us half way sometimes you know.
